FL,369,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F368A1779719227
OL,3,CJury in Ian Watkins murder trial
OL,4,Cdischarged for 'legal reasons'
OL,6,FLeeds Crown Court heard that after
OL,7,Fwalking out of the cell, Gedel handed
OL,8,Fthe makeshift knife to fellow inmate
OL,9,FSamuel Dodsworth, 44, who threw it in
OL,10,Fa bin.
OL,12,FBoth defendants denied murdering the
OL,13,F48-year-old Welshman and possessing a
OL,14,Fknife in prison.
OL,16,FOn Friday, following a trial lasting
OL,17,Ftwo weeks, the judge, Mr Justice
OL,18,FHilliard, told the jury: "Very
OL,19,Freluctantly, I'm going to discharge
OL,20,Fyou and the case will have to be re-
OL,21,Ftried.
OL,26,@zD@ZOU
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G2/6
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,369,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F368A1779719227
OL,3,CJury in Ian Watkins murder trial
OL,4,Cdischarged for 'legal reasons'
OL,6,F"That's disappointing for you and for
OL,7,Feveryone."
OL,9,FGedel told the trial he hated being
OL,10,Fhoused with sex offenders at Wakefield
OL,11,Fand had threatened to hurt "any number
OL,12,Fof paedophiles" if he was not
OL,13,Ftransferred.
OL,15,FHe said he chose Watkins largely due
OL,16,Fto "proximity", as he had been put in
OL,17,Fthe cell next to him the night before,
OL,18,Fafter being moved from another wing
OL,19,Ffor assaulting three prisoners there.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@JO]sD@\OUtD@OO]xD@DOUxD@NO]
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/6
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,369,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F368A1779719227
OL,3,CJury in Ian Watkins murder trial
OL,4,Cdischarged for 'legal reasons'
OL,6,FGedel said "part of him" wanted to
OL,7,Fkill Watkins, but another part did
OL,8,Fnot, adding: "Sometimes what your
OL,9,Fheart wants is not what your brain
OL,10,Fwants."
OL,12,FProsecutors had said Gedel and
OL,13,FDodsworth were both guilty of murder
OL,14,Fbecause Dodsworth "knew the attack was
OL,15,Fgoing to happen" and assisted Gedel by
OL,16,Fdisposing of the knife.
OL,18,FDodsworth, who is serving a sentence
OL,19,Ffor raping a woman, said he played no
OL,20,Fpart in the attack and was just in the
OL,21,Fwrong place at the wrong time.
OL,26,@nD@LOUnD@XO]pD@NOUrD@GO]vD@SOUwD@PO]
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G4/6
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
